        <p class="lead">
          When a business owner in Ahmedabad or anywhere in India asks "how much does a website cost?", the answer they get is rarely useful. You will hear 5,000 rupees from a freelancer on social media and 5 lakh from a full-service agency, and both might be quoting for essentially the same type of site. This guide breaks down exactly what drives cost, what is reasonable to expect at each price point, and how to avoid paying for what you do not need.
        </p>

        <h2 id="why-prices-vary">Why website prices vary so much in India</h2>
        <p>
          No two website quotes are based on the same assumptions. When someone says "I can build you a website for 8,000 rupees," they might mean:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>A pre-built template with your logo and text swapped in, delivered in 2 days</li>
          <li>A 3-page WordPress site with a free theme and no custom work</li>
          <li>Something built on Wix or Weebly, technically a "website" but with no code access and limited SEO control</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          When a professional agency quotes 80,000 rupees for the same request, they might include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom UI/UX design created specifically for your business</li>
          <li>Mobile-first development with SEO architecture baked in</li>
          <li>Speed optimisation targeting sub-2-second load time</li>
          <li>Content writing, Google Search Console setup, and post-launch support</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Both can be called a "business website." The price difference reflects the scope of work, not padding or dishonesty on either side.
        </p>

        <h2 id="basic-business-website">Basic business website: ₹15,000 to ₹50,000</h2>
        <p>
          A basic business website typically means 4 to 8 pages: Home, About, Services, Contact, and perhaps a Blog or FAQ page. This is suitable for most service businesses, clinics, consultants, and local shops that need an online presence and a way for customers to find and contact them.
        </p>
        <p>
          What this range typically includes at the higher end:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom design (not a template bought off the shelf)</li>
          <li>Mobile-responsive layout that works on all screen sizes</li>
          <li>Basic on-page SEO: meta titles, descriptions, proper heading structure</li>
          <li>Contact form connected to your email</li>
          <li>Google Maps integration</li>
          <li>Google Analytics and Search Console setup</li>
          <li>1 month of post-launch support</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          What this range typically does NOT include:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Advanced animations or interactive elements</li>
          <li>Content writing (you provide the text)</li>
          <li>Ongoing monthly SEO</li>
          <li>E-commerce functionality</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          For businesses in Ahmedabad looking for a clean, professional site that loads fast and ranks well in local search, this range is appropriate. Going below 15,000 rupees almost always means compromises that cost more to fix later.
        </p>

        <h2 id="ecommerce-website">E-commerce website: ₹40,000 to ₹3,00,000</h2>
        <p>
          E-commerce websites have a significantly wider price range because the complexity varies enormously based on how many products you sell, what payment methods you need, whether you need inventory management, and how customised the shopping experience needs to be.
        </p>
        <p>Here is a rough breakdown by scale:</p>
        <p>
          <strong>Small e-commerce store (10 to 50 products): ₹40,000 to ₹80,000</strong><br>
          Typically built on WooCommerce or Shopify. Standard product pages, cart, and checkout. Razorpay or PayU integration. Basic order management.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Medium e-commerce store (50 to 500 products): ₹80,000 to ₹1,50,000</strong><br>
          Includes product filters, search functionality, multiple product variants, coupon system, email order confirmations, and shipping integration.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Large e-commerce store (500+ products or custom requirements): ₹1,50,000 to ₹3,00,000+</strong><br>
          Custom-built or heavily customised platform, complex product catalogue, multi-vendor support, ERP integration, advanced analytics, and dedicated performance optimisation.
        </p>
        <p>
          For most small businesses in Gujarat starting out in e-commerce, WooCommerce on a good hosting plan (5,000 to 10,000 rupees per year) is typically more cost-effective than Shopify, which adds transaction fees of 0.5% to 2% for using third-party payment gateways like Razorpay.
        </p>

        <h2 id="landing-pages">Landing pages: ₹8,000 to ₹25,000</h2>
        <p>
          A landing page is a single-purpose page designed to convert visitors into leads or customers. Common uses include Google Ads campaigns, product launches, free consultation offers, and event registrations.
        </p>
        <p>
          Landing pages are shorter in scope than full websites but often require more care in design and copywriting because conversion is the primary goal. A landing page that converts at 5% instead of 2% can dramatically change the economics of your paid advertising campaigns.
        </p>
        <p>At 15,000 to 25,000 rupees, expect:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Custom design built around a single conversion goal</li>
          <li>Compelling headline and copy structure</li>
          <li>Lead form connected to your CRM or email</li>
          <li>Google Ads or Facebook Ads pixel integration</li>
          <li>A/B testing setup</li>
          <li>Fast load time (critical for paid traffic quality scores)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="hidden-costs">Hidden costs that catch people off guard</h2>
        <p>
          The website design fee is only part of what you will spend. These recurring and one-time costs are real and should be planned for:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Domain registration:</strong> ₹500 to ₹1,500 per year (a .in domain is cheapest, .com is more recognised)</li>
          <li><strong>Web hosting:</strong> ₹3,000 to ₹15,000 per year for shared hosting; ₹20,000+ per year for VPS or cloud hosting</li>
          <li><strong>SSL certificate:</strong> Usually included with good hosting; if not, ₹2,000 to ₹5,000 per year</li>
          <li><strong>Premium plugins or themes:</strong> If the developer is using premium tools, expect ₹3,000 to ₹15,000 upfront</li>
          <li><strong>Annual maintenance and updates:</strong> ₹10,000 to ₹30,000 per year for WordPress sites</li>
          <li><strong>Content creation:</strong> Professional photos, product photography, and copywriting are often separate from design</li>
          <li><strong>Email hosting:</strong> A professional email (name@yourcompany.com) costs ₹300 to ₹500 per user per month</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Always ask your web designer which of these are included and which are extra. A quote that seems low often excludes hosting, domain, and content.
        </p>

